Sooner or later, White would be forced to clarify the structure.} dxc5 15. Ng3
Ba6 16. Qe2 Qd7 {[%cal Gd7a4] A typical move in this structure. The threat is .
..Qa4.} ({Another option is} 16... Rf7 {[%cal Gf7d7,Gg7g6,Ge8g7] followed by ..
.Rd7. Also, Black is ready to further stabilize the kingside with ...g7-g6
followed by ...Ng7.}) 17. Rd1 {allowing ...Qa4.} ({Nevertheless,} 17. a4 {
wouldn't help after} Rd8 18. Rf3 Rf7 $19 {[%cal Gd7c6,Ga6b7,Gf7d7] Black is
totally winning. He will increase the pressure with simple moves such as ...
Qc6 followed by ...Rfd7, and ...Bb7.}) 17... Qa4 18. Nf1 Bxc4 19. Bxc4 Nxc4 $19
{Black is already winning since White does not have any compensation for the
pawn.} 20. Ne3 Nxe3 21. Bxe3 Nc7 (21... c4 22. Qf3 Nc7 23. Rd6 Rae8 $19) 22. c4
Rfd8 23. Bf2 Rac8 (23... b5 $19) 24. h4 Rxd1+ 25. Rxd1 b5 26. Rc1 Qxa3 27. Qd2
bxc4 28. Rc3 Qa4 29. Qc1 Nd5 30. Rxc4 Qb5 31. g3 a5 32. Rxc5 Rxc5 33. Bxc5 Qd3
34. Bf2 Nc3 35. Kh2 h6 36. Qa3 Qd2 37. Kg1 Ne4 38. Ba7 Qd1+ 39. Kg2 Qe2+ 40.
Kg1 Nd2 41. Bf2 Qf1+ 0-1

