{[%evp 0,40,28,28,28,13,15,15,25,-7,-12,-12,28,13,20,20,18,18,21,21,21,1,20,34,
40,-32,39,12,-6,-14,-14,-12,108,38,38,-25,4,-89,-126,-414,-446,-481,-542] Just
like in the previous example, in this game White tries to grab space in the
centre with e4-e5. This time, however, he also challenges Black's kingside
with the advance g2-g4.} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. a3 Bxc3+ 5. bxc3 c5
6. e3 b6 7. Bd3 Bb7 8. f3 Nc6 9. Ne2 O-O 10. O-O Ba6 $6 {Given the fact that
Black started with ...Bb7, this is not a logical follow-up.} ({I would have
played} 10... Na5 11. e4 Ne8 12. f4 f5) 11. e4 Ne8 12. f4 f5 {Had Black played
10...Na5 instead of 10...Ba6, the move ...f7-f5 would have been played with a
tempo.} 13. e5 $6 {White does not make use of Black's imprecise move order.} ({
Instead, he should have kept the tension with} 13. Ng3 {In the position with ..
.Na5, instead of ...Ba6, Black could have obtained a huge advantage by playing}
Nd6 $2 {In this position, however, White is better since after} 14. dxc5 bxc5
15. exf5 exf5 16. Be3 $16 {Black does not have a suitable way of protecting the
c5-pawn.}) 13... Na5 14. d5 d6 $1 {Of course! We never allow the advance d5-d6.
} {The e6-pawn will not be alive for too long.} 15. dxe6 ({It's very important
to remember that whenever White plays} 15. g4 {Black should answer it with} g6
$1 {Our pawn should be kept on f5. Otherwise, White will manage to activate
all his minor pieces. A possible line would be} 16. Ng3 Ng7 17. gxf5 gxf5 18.
Ra2 Kh8 $15 {It turns out that White does not have any kingside attack. At the
same time, his centre is rather shaky.}) 15... Qe7 16. g4 fxg4 $2 {A huge
mistake that actually grants White a winning advantage.} ({Of course, Black
should have played} 16... g6 $1 17. Ng3 Qxe6 $17 {when the c4-pawn is going to
fall. White does not have any compensation in return.}) 17. Ng3 dxe5 18. Nf5 $4
{This is actually a blunder. Now, all of a sudden, Black is winning!} ({
White should have played} 18. Qxg4 $1 Nxc4 19. fxe5 $18 {with a winning attack.
}) 18... Qxe6 19. Qxg4 e4 20. Re1 Bb7 0-1

